Collophore (
Fig. 5D
). Anterior side with about 11 chaetae, 3 proximal spine-like chaetae, 3 median mac apically acuminate, 3 mes and 2 distal mac; posterior side with 2 subapical spine-like chaetae and 1 apical smooth chaeta; lateral flap with about 11 chaetae, 7 smooth (2 of them longer than the others) and 4 ciliate.

